description:
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting an enthusiastic, responsive, practical, knowledgeable therapy assistant to work in Adult Social Care Occupational therapy services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a range of services to customers including assessments for provision of equipment, specialised equipment, manual handling equipment, adaptations, to support individuals with ADL.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work with a focus to reduce risks and enable independence or supported independence to enable customers to remain in own home, in safe environment ,either preventing need for carers/or supporting carers to meet customers needs. ASC OT work supporting the asset based approach of ensuring customers are encouraged to support themselves where possible with tasks, utilising their abilities and supporting as required to ensure they can remain at home in safe and supported way. Knowledge of equipment, minor adaptations, AT, previous knowledge of assessment of ADL and function is essential .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to communicate effectively, dealing with a range of complex communication difficulties, use of conflict resolution and remaining calm, clear and understanding of customers needs is necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working with therapy colleagues, and be supported and supervised by an experienced OT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Learning and development needs are considered and in house tutorials alongside essential training are provided. Learning from existing colleagues is key to supporting you in this role and developing your knowledge and skills further. You will work across a range of bases as require to support the service as needs require.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new and exciting opportunity for those who want to develop there skills, knowledge and career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
